## ⚙️ Hardware Requirements
| Component           |                      Description |
|---------------------|----------------------------------|
| Arduino Uno         | Main microcontroller             |
| Potentiometers (x2) | Volume and brightness control    |
| Joystick module     | Mouse movement and click         |
| SG90 Servo Motor    | RAM usage indicator              |
| LEDs (x4)           | CPU temperature indicator        |
| Jumper wires        | Connections                      |
| Breadboard          | Circuit setup                    |

## Software Requirements
 1. Operating System
    Ubuntu Linux (Recommended version: 22.04 LTS or newer)
  – Stable, long-term supported, and offers built-in serial access for Arduino.
  – Any Debian-based distro (Pop!_OS, Mint) will also work.

 2. Firmware Development Environment Environment
    | Software                                      | Purpose                                   | Notes                                 |
    | --------------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------- |
    | **Arduino IDE (v2.3.2 or newer)**             | To write and upload Arduino code to Uno   | Already compatible with Uno Rev3      |
    | **Arduino CLI (optional)**                    | Command-line upload from Linux terminal   | Useful for automation or scripting    |
    | **Python (v3.10 or newer)**                   | For Linux-side communication with Arduino | Standard in Ubuntu 22.04+             |
    | **pySerial library (`pip install pyserial`)** | Serial communication between Arduino & PC | Key component for Ubuntu-Arduino link |

  3. Supporting Packages and Tools
     | Package                            | Purpose                              | Installation Command                            |
     | ---------------------------------- | ------------------------------------ | ----------------------------------------------- |
     | **python3-pip**                    | Python package manager               | `sudo apt install python3-pip`                  |
     | **pyautogui**                      | Mouse and keyboard control           | `pip install pyautogui`                         |
     | **psutil**                         | To get RAM/CPU usage data            | `pip install psutil`                            |
     | **brightnessctl**                  | Adjust screen brightness             | `sudo apt install brightnessctl`                |
     | **pavucontrol / pulseaudio-utils** | Audio management backend             | `sudo apt install pavucontrol pulseaudio-utils` |
     | **udev rules (optional)**          | Allow non-root serial access         | `/etc/udev/rules.d/99-arduino.rules` setup      |
     

